01:16.883 --> 01:27.155
been founded. We were taking nuclear engineering 
courses, but they were being offered through the

01:27.316 --> 01:34.344
Department of Mechanical Engineering. And 
shortly thereafter, I'd say in 1960 or so, they

01:38.176 --> 01:43.364
formed the Nuclear Engineering Department. And 
that's when they brought Dr. Cochran here, not

01:44.506 --> 01:57.325
only to head up nuclear engineering, but also to be 
head of the Nuclear Science Center, which at that

01:44.506 --> 01:57.325
time was in its design phase.

02:01.531 --> 02:07.440
The studies and proposals for funding from the 
National Science Foundation the Department of

02:08.483 --> 02:17.892
Energy had all been completed and the design work 
started on the Science Center in 59. About the time

02:18.152 --> 02:24.218
I was finishing up my undergraduate work in 
mechanical engineering. So, shortly after I got

02:24.238 --> 02:36.550
into the nuclear engineering course work, I took 
an assistantship where I was assigned to the

02:24.238 --> 02:36.550
Nuclear Science Center We were housed on campus in 
the old highway research building, which is

02:37.492 --> 02:50.429
across the street from the, uh, petroleum 
engineering, the, uh, Girardi building. And we

02:50.449 --> 03:00.803
were, at that time, when I joined the science 
center, they'd already started excavation, all

02:50.449 --> 03:00.803
the construction. So I continued, uh, with my 
graduate studies, working as a half-time

03:04.643 --> 03:11.552
research assistant, or student assistant. 
Proper term, I guess, is graduate assistant. Get

03:15.376 --> 03:16.037
it right in a minute. And I stayed in that capacity 
until 1963, when I completed my studies. And then I

03:26.030 --> 03:31.697
became full-time employed at the Science Center 
as reactor supervisor. And two years after that,

03:33.010 --> 03:41.280
the administration changed at the Science 
Center. Dr. Cochran

03:41.300 --> 04:00.705
was

03:41.300 --> 04:00.705
